<TITLE> MRA starts certifying NGOs for microcredit programmes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Microcredit Regulatory Authority (MRA) has formally started issuing certificates to NGOs to ensure transparency and accountability in microcredit programmes, an official said Tuesday. In the first phase, 62 NGOs have already been issued certificates. Another 190 NGOs are scheduled to receive the certificates next week. The announcement came from a meeting of the oversight committee on microcredit activities of NGOs, chaired by MRA chairman and Bangladesh Bank governor Salehuddin Ahmed. Khandaker Mazharul Haque, assistant executive director of MRA, told reporters: "The survey on field-level activities of about 300 NGOs has already been complete. Of them, 62 have been given certificates." Officials said the MRA had decided to give certificates to 700 NGOs to run microcredit programmes with certificates being given to those NGOs that had distributed Tk 40 lakh in credit and have at least 1,000 members. A total of 5,000 NGOs applied to the MRA for certificates to run microcredit activities. bdnews24.
